cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper deals with the problem of cell segmentation in microscopy images using Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) and Convolutional Long Short Term Memory (C-LSTM) networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel approach that integrates C-LSTM with the U-Net architecture, which involves deep learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely categories as well. The use of LSTM networks also suggests cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as a possible category. Finally, the paper deals with microscopy images, which suggests cs.MM (Multimedia) as a possible category.
